I’m aware she’s trying to make it through the day and satisfy her costumers , but this is not safe given the epidemic we are currently facing around the world .

Online order pick up needs improvement.  The food is delicious and the staff are friendly but there's always a problem when I'm picking up my sandwich. I work nearby so I come in often. I always place my order on the app, and when I come to pick it up the employee is not aware about the order. It's management's responsibility to make sure there is a communication system for the employees to know about online orders.  There have been times where I waited longer for my pick-up order than I would have waited in line and ordered at the store. Ordering online (potbelly app) and picking up needs to be convenient and quick. The online pick up experience does not match other Potbelly locations.

Since moving to the West Coast, I severely miss having Potbelly regularly. Their sandwiches are so good! I got the mushroom melt with all the toppings, and it hit the spot. And despite being crazy busy with the teacher strike, the employees were fast and friendly. I will visit every time I'm traveling somewhere there's a Potbelly's :)
Great sandwiches.

Josh C is amazing my order was wrong and  he personally  brought my sandwich to me. In addition to this, when i talked to him about my issue his over the phone his customer service was incredible. Thank you again and I definitely would recommend this location.

Tasty sandwiches, with the perfect ratio between meat, veggies and bread.  Definitely waaaay better than Subway.  Plus, the staff is always very friendly and efficient, even when the line is out the door. I always drop by at least once whenever I'm in Chicago.
